===Noun===
'''[[Pinyin]]''' also '''pinyin'''<!--Collins only gives upper, M-W only gives lower, Encarta gives both but puts upper first-->

# A system of [[romanization]] (phonetic notation and transliteration to roman script) for [[Mandarin]] that is used in the [[People's Republic of China]]. It helps with pronouncing Chinese characters. Consists of over 70 irregular "[[sounds]]" (not including accents) of [[vowel|vowels]], [[consonant]]s, and [[sounds]] that are irregular. Uses 5 different accents for each [[vowel]]: Ex: a: ā, á, ǎ, à, a

==== Translations ====
*Chinese: [[拼音]] ([[Pīnyīn]])
*Japanese: [[ピンイン]] (pin'in)

